NBA former player Jason Williams during the All-Star Celebrity Game at Mercedes-Benz Superdome. (Photo: Derick E. Hingle-USA TODAY Sport) 
Jason Williams busted out the old elbow pass in the NBA All-Star Celebrity Game on Friday night. It was fumbled a bit because no one saw it coming, but it was great nonetheless. White Chocolate's still got it! #NBACelebGame pic.twitter.com/mSPCTzkboG 
White Chocolate also easily shook off Romeo Miller on his way to the hoop on another play. Will the 41-year-old ever lose his touch? Lil Romeo tried to guard Jason Williams and it didn't go well pic.twitter.com/cKKBV8AfyT 
Williams' team, the East, cruised to an easy 88-59 win. Read or Share this story: http://ftw.usatoday.com/2017/02/jason-williams-elbow-pass-assist-nba-all-star-celebrity-game-win-video/ Most Popular
